         Job Description
          Drive the product development initiatives around using data to drive patient activation and clinical decisions
          Define and develop predictive models to drive customer engagement and positive health outcomes using data sets from medical devices, clinical data, and electronic medical records
          Work on challenging fundamental data science problems in medical applications
          Propose and develop solutions independently and lead a group of other data scientists
          Develop a scalable A/B testing framework and process for evaluating changes to the user experience and features in terms of specific engagement or clinical outcomes
          Communicate findings to product managers and engineers
          Drive the collection and curation of new data and the refinement of existing data sources
         Qualifications
          Master’s Degree or PhD in a relevant technical field (machine learning, computer science, physics, mathematics, statistics, etc.)
          5 years of experience in building and leading a team focused on quantitative analysis
          Extensive experience solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches using machine learning methods
          Solid track record of using advanced statistical methods, information retrieval, and data mining techniques
          Comfortable manipulating and analyzing complex data from varying sources
          Able to communicate complex quantitative analyses in a clear, precise, and actionable manner
          Fluency with Python and Spark
          Familiarity with AWS EMR, Kinesis, S3, and Redshift
          Superb verbal and written communication skills
          Excellent organizational skills along with strong attention to detail
          Ability to work both independently and collaboratively with small, cross-functional teams
           Reasoning Ability
          Ability to apply principles of logical thinking to a wide range of intellectual and practical problems.
